<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12005k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12005k">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12005k"> 5(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> the hunt (stones) <font face="wake">O</font></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> &ccedil;a vous repr&eacute;sente un duc qui voulait tuer un cerf le jour de P&acirc;ques. Il partit d&egrave;s le matin avec tout son monde et, n&apos;ayant point entendu sonner les cloches de sa paroisse et par cons&eacute;quent n&apos;ayant pas eu de messe, il fut par punition <mark>chang&eacute; en pierre, lui et toute la chasse</mark>. <br]<font color="green">[&hellip; this depicts for you a duke who wanted to kill a stag at Easter. He left in the morning with all his people and he did not hear his parish bells ring and consequently missed mass. He was punished by being changed into stone, along with all his hunting party.]</font> <small> l'Abb&eacute; A. Millon, <a name="AMPB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AMPB"><cite title="source">Pauvres Pierres! Les Megalithes Bretons devant la science</cite></a> (n.d) 17</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
